  "prompt": "How do I disconnect/deactivate a postpaid connection in India? Can they come after me legally if I just break the SIM and not bother?",
  "response": "To disconnect a postpaid mobile connection in India, you should follow these steps:\n\n1. Official Procedure:\n- Visit the service provider's store or customer service center\n- Bring your original ID proof and connection documents\n- Submit a disconnection request form\n- Clear any pending bills\n- Get a disconnection confirmation\n\n2. Alternative Methods:\n- Call customer care\n- Send a written request via email\n- Use online portal/app of your service provider\n\n3. Legal Implications of Just Breaking SIM:\n- Not recommended\n- You'll continue to be liable for:\n  * Pending bills\n  * Early termination charges\n  * Potential legal notice for contract breach\n  * Negative credit report impact\n\n4. Potential Consequences of Ignoring:\n- Service provider may:\n  * Send legal notice\n  * Initiate recovery proceedings\n  * Report to credit bureaus\n  * Impose penalties\n\n5. Best Practice:\n- Always formally disconnect through official channels\n- Obtain written confirmation of disconnection\n- Clear all outstanding dues\n- Keep disconnection proof for future reference\n\nRecommendation: Follow official disconnection procedure to avoid legal complications.",
